<i>Posted by Torrn on 03-25-2003 04:13 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Immy is right.  SB is far from perfect, but they HAVE gotten quite a bit of the lag problems fixed.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
But you also have to realize that, while the graphics are pretty crappy, you get a LOT of graphical lag (It's not just server lag)<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
It's strange, though.  I'm able to run around a large group of people with zero slow down.  But if I go into a larger city, it's like playing DoomIII on a 286 with a 2mb video card.<br />
<br />
<br />
My own complaints:<br />
<br />
Lag that I listed above.<br />
<br />
<br />
The movement system (Click where you want to go)<br />
<br />
<br />
The lay of the land.  It's mostly flat expanses with mobs placed randomly about.  No variation.  That's why I liked EQ's graphics over DAOC's.  DAoC was dull, drab, no color, everything looked the same.  EQ's zones, for the most part, varied greatly from zone line to zone line.  SB is an isometric DAoC.<br />
<br />
<br />
The graphics are actually the SAME as DAoC in every way except character models.<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
